summary: An Ordinance accepting a deed to the City of Seattle executed on December 24, 1910, by the Seattle Lighting Company, a private corporation, for Lot 1, Block 1; and part of Lot 2, Block 1; Lots 1, 2, 3, 10 and 11, Block 2; and part of Lots 4, 8 and 9, Block 2; part of Lots 5, 6, 7 and 8, Block 2; Lot 6 and part of Lot 5, Block 6, Burke's First Addition; part of vacated north Twenty-ninth Street lying east of the east line of Wallingofrd Avenue and west of the west line produced south of Lot 10, Block 3, in Supplemental Plat of Block 3, Burke's First Addition; part of Lots 11 and 12, Block 3, in Supplemental Plat of Block 3, Burke's First Addition; part of Block 9, Burke's First Addition; and part of Block 44, Plat of Lake Union Shore Lands and part of Nortlake Avenue lying east of the east line of Wallingford Avenue and west of the west line produced south of Lot 10, Block 3, Supplemental Plat of Block 3, Burke's First Addition to the City of Seattle.
